{
  "stem": "26142.5",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But it turned out that it was a paper tiger at that time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "So we stayed there, and these soldiers, Jewish soldiers from the [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH], when they saw that here are whole families coming in, they didn't know.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "They were out there before.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "They didn't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Some of them found out that their own families were taken away.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "So you can imagine what they felt like.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Anyway, we got unloaded again in there, and we started loading up on military trucks.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And military trucks, the same thing again happened, that people tried to stay and stick together.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And I remember distinctly that my uncle, my only-- my father's only brother, and his son, daughter, and granddaughter-- a little darling girl, three years old-- and another cousin of my father's family, they tried very hard to stick with us together on the truck, and they were terribly beaten up and put on other trucks.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And we were talking to-- we managed.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "I was 21 years old.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "My other brother was 33, and Moshe was still in the early 40s, so we were able to hustle up and get up on those trucks, and be together, try to keep together by force-- we forced ourselves.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And that determined our fate.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "My father's brother, his family, my father's sister, her family-- that's what we saw there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "They were put up on other trucks, and we were put up-- and that determined our fate, life or death, survive or not.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because from there, they shipped us over across the Dniester River.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Dniester is one of the major rivers in Europe.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You have the Vistula River, and the Danube River, the Dnieper River, and the Volga river.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Those are major rivers that flow across Europe.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They put us across the Dniester river.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
